article_title: The 10-Point: Gerard Baker on New Laws, Market Winners, Air-Travelling Resolutions, and More
article_text:
Hello,

For Better or for Worse

The Affordable Care Act is officially reshaping the U.S. health-care system, whether Americans like it or not. We find that the true test this year will be to see whether the new system provides coverage to people whose medical conditions, income level or personal choice previously left them without insurance. So far, we've noted troubling signs, namely a concern that insurers will withdraw plans if the enrollment of older, sicker patients continues to outpace that of younger, healthier...
